Yobe State Governor, Mai Mala Buni, has congratulated Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, for emerging as the presidential flag bearer of the All Progressives Congress (APC). In a statement via his Director-General Press and Media Affairs, Mamman Mohammed, Gov. Buni described Tinubu as a well-grounded politician who can lead APC to victory in the 2023 general election. He urged former aspirants to join hands with Tinubu to ensure the success of the party in the presidential election come 2023. In his words, Buni said, “The Primary election is over, we should all rally round our Presidential candidate to ensure the party’s victory in the general election.” The ex-APC Caretaker Chairman enjoined former aspirants to embrace the spirit of sportsmanship for the unity and success of the party.